{
  "comment_text": {
    "snp1.12:3.1": "Taking <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pamāya</i> as an absolutive of <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pamiṇāti</i> per <a href='https://suttacentral.net/snp4.12/en/sujato#17.1'>Snp 4.12:17.1</a>, against the commentary’s sense of “crushed” (Sanskrit: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pramṛṇati</i>). ",
    "snp1.12:3.4": "Compare the stock idiom <i lang='pi' translate='no'>Saṅkhampi na upeti</i> at eg. <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn20.2/en/sujato#1.7'>SN 20.2:1.7</a>; also <a href='https://suttacentral.net/snp5.7/en/sujato#6.3'>Snp 5.7:6.3</a>. "
  },
