  "root_text": {
    "snp1.12:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 1.12 ",
    "snp1.12:0.2": "Munisutta ",
    "snp1.12:1.1": "Santhavāto bhayaṁ jātaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:1.2": "niketā jāyate rajo; ",
    "snp1.12:1.3": "Aniketamasanthavaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:1.4": "etaṁ ve munidassanaṁ. ",
    "snp1.12:2.1": "Yo jātamucchijja na ropayeyya, ",
    "snp1.12:2.2": "Jāyantamassa nānuppavecche; ",
    "snp1.12:2.3": "Tamāhu ekaṁ muninaṁ carantaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:2.4": "Addakkhi so santipadaṁ mahesi. ",
    "snp1.12:3.1": "Saṅkhāya vatthūni pamāya bījaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:3.2": "Sinehamassa nānuppavecche; ",
    "snp1.12:3.3": "Sa ve munī jātikhayantadassī, ",
    "snp1.12:3.4": "Takkaṁ pahāya na upeti saṅkhaṁ. ",
    "snp1.12:4.1": "Aññāya sabbāni nivesanāni, ",
    "snp1.12:4.2": "Anikāmayaṁ aññatarampi tesaṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:4.3": "Sa ve munī vītagedho agiddho, ",
    "snp1.12:4.4": "Nāyūhatī pāragato hi hoti. ",
    "snp1.12:5.1": "Sabbābhibhuṁ sabbaviduṁ sumedhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:5.2": "Sabbesu dhammesu anūpalittaṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:5.3": "Sabbañjahaṁ taṇhakkhaye vimuttaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:5.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:6.1": "Paññābalaṁ sīlavatūpapannaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:6.2": "Samāhitaṁ jhānarataṁ satīmaṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:6.3": "Saṅgā pamuttaṁ akhilaṁ anāsavaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:6.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:7.1": "Ekaṁ carantaṁ munimappamattaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:7.2": "Nindāpasaṁsāsu avedhamānaṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:7.3": "Sīhaṁva saddesu asantasantaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:7.4": "Vātaṁva jālamhi asajjamānaṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:7.5": "Padmaṁva toyena alippamānaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:7.6": "Netāramaññesamanaññaneyyaṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:7.7": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:8.1": "Yo ogahaṇe thambhorivābhijāyati, ",
    "snp1.12:8.2": "Yasmiṁ pare vācāpariyantaṁ vadanti; ",
    "snp1.12:8.3": "Taṁ vītarāgaṁ susamāhitindriyaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:8.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:9.1": "Yo ve ṭhitatto tasaraṁva ujju, ",
    "snp1.12:9.2": "Jigucchati kammehi pāpakehi; ",
    "snp1.12:9.3": "Vīmaṁsamāno visamaṁ samañca, ",
    "snp1.12:9.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:10.1": "Yo saññatatto na karoti pāpaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:10.2": "Daharo majjhimo ca muni yatatto; ",
    "snp1.12:10.3": "Arosaneyyo na so roseti kañci, ",
    "snp1.12:10.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:11.1": "Yadaggato majjhato sesato vā, ",
    "snp1.12:11.2": "Piṇḍaṁ labhetha paradattūpajīvī; ",
    "snp1.12:11.3": "Nālaṁ thutuṁ nopi nipaccavādī, ",
    "snp1.12:11.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:12.1": "Muniṁ carantaṁ virataṁ methunasmā, ",
    "snp1.12:12.2": "Yo yobbane nopanibajjhate kvaci; ",
    "snp1.12:12.3": "Madappamādā virataṁ vippamuttaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:12.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:13.1": "Aññāya lokaṁ paramatthadassiṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:13.2": "Oghaṁ samuddaṁ atitariya tādiṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:13.3": "Taṁ chinnaganthaṁ asitaṁ anāsavaṁ, ",
    "snp1.12:13.4": "Taṁ vāpi dhīrā muni vedayanti. ",
    "snp1.12:14.1": "Asamā ubho dūravihāravuttino, ",
    "snp1.12:14.2": "Gihī dāraposī amamo ca subbato; ",
    "snp1.12:14.3": "Parapāṇarodhāya gihī asaññato, ",
    "snp1.12:14.4": "Niccaṁ munī rakkhati pāṇine yato. ",
    "snp1.12:15.1": "Sikhī yathā nīlagīvo vihaṅgamo, ",
    "snp1.12:15.2": "Haṁsassa nopeti javaṁ kudācanaṁ; ",
    "snp1.12:15.3": "Evaṁ gihī nānukaroti bhikkhuno, ",
    "snp1.12:15.4": "Munino vivittassa vanamhi jhāyatoti. ",
    "snp1.12:15.5": "Munisuttaṁ dvādasamaṁ. ",
    "snp1.12:15.6": "Uragavaggo paṭhamo. ",
    "snp1.12:16.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "snp1.12:16.1": "Urago dhaniyo ceva, ",
    "snp1.12:16.2": "visāṇañca tathā kasi; ",
    "snp1.12:16.3": "Cundo parābhavo ceva, ",
    "snp1.12:16.4": "vasalo mettabhāvanā. ",
    "snp1.12:17.1": "Sātāgiro āḷavako, ",
    "snp1.12:17.2": "Vijayo ca tathā muni; ",
    "snp1.12:17.3": "Dvādasetāni suttāni, ",
    "snp1.12:17.4": "Uragavaggoti vuccatīti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp1.12:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 1.12 ",
    "snp1.12:0.2": "The Sage ",
    "snp1.12:1.1": "Peril stems from intimacy, ",
    "snp1.12:1.2": "dust comes from an abode. ",
    "snp1.12:1.3": "Freedom from abode and intimacy: ",
    "snp1.12:1.4": "that is the sage’s vision. ",
    "snp1.12:2.1": "Having cut down what’s grown, <j>they wouldn’t replant, ",
    "snp1.12:2.2": "nor would they nurture what’s growing. ",
    "snp1.12:2.3": "That’s who they call a sage wandering alone, ",
    "snp1.12:2.4": "the great seer has seen the state of peace. ",
    "snp1.12:3.1": "Having appraised the fields and measured the seeds, ",
    "snp1.12:3.2": "they wouldn’t nurture them with moisture. ",
    "snp1.12:3.3": "Truly that sage who sees the ending of rebirth ",
    "snp1.12:3.4": "has left speculation behind and is beyond reckoning. ",
    "snp1.12:4.1": "Understanding all the planes of rebirth, ",
    "snp1.12:4.2": "not wanting a single one of them, ",
    "snp1.12:4.3": "Truly that sage freed of greed ",
    "snp1.12:4.4": "need not swim, <j>for they have reached the far shore. ",
    "snp1.12:5.1": "The champion, all-knower, so very intelligent, ",
    "snp1.12:5.2": "unsullied in the midst of all things, ",
    "snp1.12:5.3": "has given up all, freed in the ending of craving: ",
    "snp1.12:5.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:6.1": "Strong in wisdom, <j>with precepts and observances intact, ",
    "snp1.12:6.2": "serene, loving absorption, mindful, ",
    "snp1.12:6.3": "released from chains, kind, undefiled: ",
    "snp1.12:6.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:7.1": "The diligent sage wandering alone, ",
    "snp1.12:7.2": "is unshaken by blame and praise—",
    "snp1.12:7.3": "like a lion not startled by sounds, ",
    "snp1.12:7.4": "like wind not caught in a net, ",
    "snp1.12:7.5": "like water not sticking to a lotus. ",
    "snp1.12:7.6": "Leader of others, not by others led: ",
    "snp1.12:7.7": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:8.1": "Steady as a post in a bathing-place ",
    "snp1.12:8.2": "when others speak endlessly against them, ",
    "snp1.12:8.3": "freed of greed, with senses stilled: ",
    "snp1.12:8.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:9.1": "Steadfast, straight as a shuttle, ",
    "snp1.12:9.2": "horrified by wicked deeds, ",
    "snp1.12:9.3": "discerning the just and the unjust: ",
    "snp1.12:9.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:10.1": "Restrained, they do no evil, ",
    "snp1.12:10.2": "young or middle-aged, the sage is self-controlled. ",
    "snp1.12:10.3": "Irreproachable, he does not insult anyone: ",
    "snp1.12:10.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:11.1": "When one who lives on charity receives alms, ",
    "snp1.12:11.2": "from the top, the middle, or the leftovers, ",
    "snp1.12:11.3": "they think it unworthy to praise or put down: ",
    "snp1.12:11.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:12.1": "The sage lives refraining from sex, ",
    "snp1.12:12.2": "even when young is not tied down, ",
    "snp1.12:12.3": "refraining from indulgence and negligence, freed: ",
    "snp1.12:12.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:13.1": "Understanding the world, <j>the seer of the ultimate goal, ",
    "snp1.12:13.2": "the unaffected one, <j>having crossed the flood and the ocean, ",
    "snp1.12:13.3": "has cut the ties, unattached and undefiled: ",
    "snp1.12:13.4": "that’s who the attentive know as a sage. ",
    "snp1.12:14.1": "The two are not the same, <j>far apart in lifestyle and conduct—",
    "snp1.12:14.2": "the householder providing for a wife, <j>and the selfless one true to their vows. ",
    "snp1.12:14.3": "The unrestrained householder kills other creatures, ",
    "snp1.12:14.4": "while the restrained sage <j>always protects living creatures. ",
    "snp1.12:15.1": "As the crested blue-necked peacock <j>flying through the sky ",
    "snp1.12:15.2": "never approaches the speed of the swan, ",
    "snp1.12:15.3": "so the householder cannot compete <j>with the mendicant, ",
    "snp1.12:15.4": "the sage meditating secluded in the woods. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp1.12:1.1": "Santhavāto → sandhavato (mr) ",
    "snp1.12:1.4": "muni → muniṁ (bj, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp1.12:3.1": "pamāya → pahāya (bj, mr); samāya (katthaci) ",
    "snp1.12:7.5": "Padmaṁva → padumaṁva (bj, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) | alippamānaṁ → alimpamānaṁ (sya-all, mr) ",
    "snp1.12:8.2": "vācāpariyantaṁ → vācaṁ pariyantaṁ (mr) ",
    "snp1.12:10.2": "Daharo majjhimo ca muni → daharo ca majjhimo ca munī (bj); daharo ca majjho ca munī (sya-all, km, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp1.12:10.3": "na so roseti → so na roseti (bj, pts-vp-pli1); na roseti (sya-all) ",
    "snp1.12:14.2": "Gihī → gihi (mr) ",
    "snp1.12:14.4": "pāṇine → pāṇino (bj) ",
    "snp1.12:15.1": "nīlagīvo → nīlagivo (sya-all) "
  },
